node.text: Tears of reflection on this road to liberation. My heart hurts but when I hear the beautiful words of artists like my special friend @terisasiagatonu or my angel @ajamonet my heart is reminded that we aren’t alone in wanting a better world, we aren’t idealist...we are actively moving towards a reckoning. We must honor our stories. We must honor theirs. In honor of the 215 native babies that were found this week on the site of the Kamloops Indian Residential School. Children kidnapped from Tk'emlúps te Secwépemc First Nation in what is known as BC Canada. My heart is with the families. My mind can not comprehend the amount of pain involved in having your children kidnapped by systems and finding out they endured this kind of pain. I encourage you to look at my stories and read the article if you haven’t. Trigger warning: it is terrifyingly violent what has been done and what continues to happen to indigenous children and people across lands. The violence that is settler colonialism is sinister, deep rooted and in my opinion a sort of spiritual warfare. There is no justification for the abuse of children. There is no justification for abuse of power. There is no justification for their wars; they are consistently for the profit of a few wealthy men. We deserve freedom. We deserve to recognize the collective struggle of people everywhere and these babies deserve reparations and their land back. Solidarity with indigenous people EVERYWHERE. My heart aches but visions as potent as the beautiful freedom fighters Im proud to call friends keep me alive in spirit. Thank you for you words hermana, I love you @terisasiagatonu

node.text: Listen, Read, watch. I am grateful every single day for the breath in my lungs and the abundance of life. For my friends and family, for you all, for my health, for the ability to take each moment as a new opportunity to connect to my higher self; there are actually endless things that I’m grateful for every single day because I am beyond privileged and blessed. I am always grateful to connect with my family for a beautiful meal together especially during this time where we have not been able to spend time that we normally do. However, this is not something we should reserve for celebrating genocide, especially when that genocide extends to this very day. My heart and solidarity is with all Native/Indigenous peoples of this Earth who were decimated by colonization and who’s descendants are still persecuted today; especially the array of tribal nations that made/make up Turtle Island (what we call the USA) I honor you, your ancestors and the descendants of the seven generations to come. They are still here, they are still deserving of their land back and control over the stewardship of it in order for us to actually address the climate crisis we face. The wisdom they impart about life and our connection with everything around us is what deserves celebration and thanks-giving. Some food for thought.

node.text:
I love watching dancers embody music. One of the most mesmerizing and therapeutic things for me is to dance and watch dance move through people. To inspire anyone to move this beautifully with words I wrote from my heart is the biggest blessing in the world. This choreo is so beautiful mama, and your caption brought a hug to my heart through the distance. Sending you love! 

Dancer: @kaylamaria.g 
Song: 50ft. by @laurenjauregui

4. Align yourself with Spirit (God, Allah, Yaweh, whatever you call creator) and get to work on yourself so we can shift this collective consciousness and elevate our vibration past all this toxic nonsense.
5. I love you. 
Goodnight.

You’re actually one of my favorite songstresses of this generation. People don’t even know the amount of work you’ve put in or how many songs they love are from YOUR heart. You’re one of the most creative writers ever and ur melodies are on STUPID and ur also my favorite vocal producer I’ve ever worked with and ur fine af so. All that aside though, you’re also gem of a human being w that heart. I sing this song all the damn time and so I figured I’d cover it in case y’all for forgot I could sing 😂 (listen with earbuds/AirPods/headphones for the best quality bih)

LOVE YOU VIC

node.text: You GUYSSSSS this beautiful piece was created for me by this angel and I sincerely am moved to tears by its beauty. I can’t even handle how beautiful she is; made her way straight to my altar. Thank you SOUL MUCH MONA!! @the.prickly.pear your creative vision and love of plants are such a sick combo! I will cherish this gift forever and ever!! I also especially loved the sustainable packaging!! It’s biodegradable paper with wildflower seeds packed into them so they can be replanted in a garden🥰😍 thoughtful and eco-friendly (PS my shirt is by @anti.giampiero )

node.text: So excited for my brilliant friend @dianewarren !! The Cave Sessions Vol. 1 is available August 27th and the link for the preorder is in my story✨ So grateful to be a part of this project and for your unwavering belief in my talent. You are a legend and I’m so honored that you chose me along side these incredible artists to be a part of this special project❤️ you’re a gem! Powerful women ftw✨

node.text: Feliz cumpleaños Abuelito🥰 que emoción anoche con familia y la cantidad de amor y felicidad que tu vida inspira en nosotros. Aunque ya no puedes pararte pa bailar con todo el mundo, esa manito nunca paro de moverse. El ritmo vive en tu sangre y aunque tu mente esté en otro lado, a veces nos miramos con una familiaridad que transciende el cuerpo y esta vida..y se que bailáramos otra vez algún día. Gracias por todo lo que me has enseñado. Me alegro tanto haber podido celebrarte ayer y espero unos mas🥺💞 te amo abuelito✨

node.text:
My heart is with all of the people in Cuba in this moment. The people deserve freedom from the dictatorship. The people deserve resources and freedom of speech and protest. Food, medicine, access!! I also want to point out that the US Embargo doesn’t help the situation in the slightest and that US intervention isn’t going to be the savior to this situation. It’s important to look at the situation with critical thought // Mi corazón está con la gente de Cuba en este momento. La gente merecen libertad de la dictadura. La gente merecen el derecho de libertad de expresión y protesta. Comida, medicina, acceso coño!! También quiero apuntar que el embargo de los Estados Unidos sobre Cuba no ayuda la situación y que la intervención de los Estados Unidos no es la solución que creen que es. Es importante observar lo que está pasando con una mente crítica. 🇨🇺CUBA LIBRE!! #PatriayVida #SOSCuba mandando amor y fuerza🇨🇺

My mother and my grandparents on both sides were born on the island. My fathers family in Havana and my mothers from Matanzas. I am very proud of the strong connection I have with my roots and my ancestors. They deserve to see through my eyes Cuba, finally, free🇨🇺 //
Mi mamá y mis abuelos por los dos lados nacieron en la isla. La familia de mi papá en La Habana y la familia de mi madre en Matanzas. Siento much orgullo de tener una conexión fuerte con mis raizes y ancestros. Merecen ver  a través de mis ojos de donde están que Cuba, al fin, libre🇨🇺 
📷: @efeamerica

node.text: Big Femme Energy: an all female compilation album by @femmeitforward streaming everywhere now! My song #WhileImAlive is an ode to all the assholes who tried to tell me who I was or what kinda art I should’ve been giving the world, or how I should’ve been behaving. Sending you all love and blessings as I rise from your lies.✨ enjoy and take a deep listen to all these magical co-collaborators❤️✨ I love women (also huge shout out to @alberthype for that epic guitar solo and helping me bring this to life✨)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Lauren Jauregui on July 08, 2021. May be an image of 5 people, child and indoor.

node.text: So grateful to be a part of this beautiful piece of art. Songs by women who are so deeply connected with their craft and truth. I feel deeply that when we women share our truths— with ourselves, one another, and especially together—we heal. Thank you to all of the incredible women & folks who came together to create this visually and sonically✨ Im honored to be a part of your beautiful vision @heatherlowery . This song was one I wasn’t sure the world was ever gonna hear. It’s quite personal and was written from a vulnerable place of being completely tired of being told who the fuck I am and who I’m supposed to be in order to be successful in this industry. It was written to someone, but at the end of it, like most of my songs, it was really just about me and making sure I was reminded of the power of my vulnerability and truth, no matter what anyone has to say about it in this judgmental ass world. I hope it empowers you to feel seen. #BigFemmeEnergy @FemmeItForward

node.text:
I love rain showers.. thunderstorms...seeing the lightening move so quickly and violently and beautifully through the sky. I don’t know why but they’ve always made me feel calm, even when the thunder was particularly upset. The sound of rain hitting the things we’ve made, yes, while I sit at home or in a car seat and watch it through the window panes between us. It was one of the reasons I couldn’t see myself living in California forever. It never rains. I need the rain. They tell us to stay out of it, that it ruins a sunny day but one thing about Miami is it’s gonna have its aguaseros and it’s descansos. Quince minutos si lo puedes soportar..and I prefer to wait it out in the water. On my birthday this year, the sun made a glorious appearance and kept me warm and the water refreshing..but the rain also stopped by to say hello and wish me a new year of life...offering me it’s cleansing. Fresh meeting salt..floating in the vast expansiveness that is Yemaya’s waters. It felt right. I feel most alive here. I feel held here..by the buoyancy of the water..by the spirits of my grandmothers and their mothers mothers. The water, in all its forms, reminds me we all belong to something greater and feeling it’s caress will always feel like home. 

((tell me you’re a water sign without telling me you’re a water sign))
